                <fr:title text="Wild initial objects from universal cones">Wild initial objects from universal cones</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-0037.xml" title="Wild category" addr="jms-0037" type="local">wild category</fr:link>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I:\mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex> be an object of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex>. If we may equip a <fr:link href="jms-0039.xml" title="Wild natural transformation" addr="jms-0039" type="local">wild natural transformation</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Delta  I}\xrightarrow {{\alpha }}{1_{\mathcal {C}}}]]></fr:tex> from the <fr:link href="jms-003D.xml" title="The wild constant functor" addr="jms-003D" type="local">constant 0-functor</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathcal {C}}\xrightarrow {{\Delta  I}}{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex> to the <fr:link href="jms-003C.xml" title="The wild identity functor" addr="jms-003C" type="local">identity 0-functor</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathcal {C}}\xrightarrow {{1_{\mathcal {C}}}}{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex> with an identification <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[c_\alpha  : \alpha _I = 1_{I}]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (I,A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is contractible for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A:\mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>(Our proof will follow that of the <fr:link href="https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/initial+object" type="external">nLab</fr:link>, which was stated for ordinary categories and functors and natural transformations rather than wild ones. It was <fr:link href="mikeshulman.xml" title="Mike Shulman" addr="mikeshulman" type="local">Mike Shulman</fr:link> who <fr:link href="https://homotopytypetheory.org/2018/11/26/impredicative-encodings-part-3/" type="external">noticed</fr:link> who noticed that this proof also works for the wild/incoherent notions studied here.)</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>3</fr:month><fr:day>14</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>10548</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/5966</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-5966.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>To show that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (I,A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is contractible, we choose <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{A} : \mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (I,A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> as the center of contraction. To identify any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : \mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (I,A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{A}]]></fr:tex>, we use the <fr:link href="jms-0039.xml" title="Wild natural transformation" addr="jms-0039" type="local">wild naturality</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\Delta  I}\xrightarrow {{\alpha }}{1_{\mathcal {C}}}]]></fr:tex>. In particular, we have an identification <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _f]]></fr:tex> between <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _I;f]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{I};\alpha _A]]></fr:tex>. By our assumption that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _I=1_{I}]]></fr:tex> and using the <fr:link href="jms-0037.xml" title="Wild category" addr="jms-0037" type="local">wild left-unit</fr:link> identifications <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda  f]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda  \alpha _A]]></fr:tex>, we may identify <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _A]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
