            <fr:title text="Wild natural transformation">Wild natural transformation</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C},\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:link href="jms-0037.xml" title="Wild category" addr="jms-0037" type="local">wild categories</fr:link>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F,G:\mathcal {C}\to \mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> be two
  <fr:link href="jms-0038.xml" title="Wild 0-functor" addr="jms-0038" type="local">wild 0-functors</fr:link> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex>. A <fr:em>wild natural transformation</fr:em> is defined by the following data:</fr:p>
            <fr:ol><fr:li>for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A:\mathbf {ob}_{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex>, an element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{A} : \mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {D}}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathbf {ob}_{F}A,\mathbf {ob}_{G}A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f:\mathbf {hom}_{\mathcal {C}}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, an identification <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{f} : \alpha _A; \mathbf {hom}_{G}{f} = \mathbf {hom}_{F}{f};\alpha _B]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
          </fr:mainmatter>
